==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shell-lac
<hw>Shell"-lac`</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Shell</ets> + <ets>lac</ets> a resinous
substance; cf. D. <ets>shellak</ets>, G. <ets>schellack</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Lac which has been reduced to a thin crust. See the
Note under 2d <er>Lac</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A solution of shellac{1} in alcohol or other
volatile solvent, used as a varnish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A phonograph record, made of a material containing
shellac; -- no longer manufactured.</def> <mark>[Obsolescent]</mark>
<au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shellapple</ent>⟦br⟧
